          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation, study, and recitation and is a late Vedic philosophical treatise on the attainment of divine knowledge and the importance and significance of Vedic mantras and words, their recitation, and how they lead to the realization of higher truths, such as the brahman, the ultimate principle in the universe. This text especially focuses on pronunciation. Work contains an unidentified commentary, possibly by Damodāra.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
